	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Tue, Dec 18th 12:29 PM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Excellent<span id=notbold>[5.00]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>I was first introduced to the Ghoulbane when I was of 17th or 18th rank.  It was given to me by an elder Paladin, whom I did not know.  This gift has been a treasure.  What a wonderful weapon to attain.  The ~135 DD VS Undead proc kept me cleansing the world of evil quite nicely.  Even after hitting 30, I did not seek out another weapon because I did not want to loose my undead smash.<br><br>Now I have Instrument of Nife.  With this, any weapon procs nearly twice as hard (~220 DD) vs undead as the Ghoulbane.<br><br>Last night I went hunting Giant Skeletons in Rathe Mountains, with my Ghoulbane and Instrument of Nife cast.  Now, I only got to kill 4 skellies (due to server outage most of the evening), but in that time Instrument of Nife proc'd 7 times and the Ghoulbane proc'd none.  I realize this is a short test, but on average my Ghoulbane would attempt to proc three to four times per fight.  All this leads me to believe that the Ghoulbane proc and Instrument of Nife do not stack.<br><br>Now, here comes the quandary...<br><br>Whether by camp or by quest, you will need to be level 30, or very close to it, in order to collect a Ghoulbane.  But Instrument of Nife is a level 30 spell.  So when would you ever use the Ghoulbane in battle?  By level 30 you should be able to acquire a stronger sword (dmg/dly) than the Ghoulbane.  Previously, we Paladins would forego the increased dmg/dly of another sword in favor of the undead proc.  Now there is no reason for this.<br><br>So while there may still be quest related reasons to COLLECT the Ghoulbane, why would you ever USE it?<br><br>It seems to me that either the sword should be made more readily available to Paladins in their late teens to 20s (those to whom the sword is really useful) or the two procs should stack, maintaining the weapons usefulness to those over 30.<br><br>Just some thoughts...<br><br>&nbsp;<br>-Maintaining the Honor of Test</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 >&nbsp;</td><td align=right valign=bottom>
	   <span style='font-weight: normal; font-size: 9px;'>[<a href=#top>Top</a>]</span></tr>
