<table  border=0 cellpadding=2 cellspacing=0 awidth=100%><a name=100946276736909></a><form action=http://eqdb.allakhazam.com/strategy/mrate.pl name=f100946276736909><tr><td id=headerrow><a id=sj href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100946276736909>RE: Ghoulbane Lost it's Luster??</a> <a id=fs8 href=classes.html?class=6&mid=100946276736909#post><img src=http://everquest.allakhazam.com/static/reply.gif border=0 alt="Reply..." height=16 width=16></a></td><td align=right id=headerrow valign=bottom><span id=notbold>By:</span> <a href=poster.html?user=122954><span id= >Runtiss</span></a>, <span id= > </span><br><span id=notbold>4 posts</td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=1 id=headerrow>Posted @ Thu, Dec 27th 9:19 AM 2001</td>
	   <td id=headerrow align=right><span id=notbold>Score</span>: Good<span id=notbold>[3.50]</span></td></tr>
	   <tr><td colspan=2>Hello all.... I am Runtiss Abigone (Blade &amp; Magic)Level 32 Palidan,Drinal Server <br><br>A few thought and observations of one of the newer Pally buffs... <br><br>I have been hunting in the basement of Unrest for a little while now .. helping fellow guildies with obtaining Dwarven work boots from the General. I have been using the Ghoulbane as my primary against undead w/ Nife buff, I noticed that the Ghoul did not proc as much and the Nife did not proc that often as well. The Ghoul was doing 158dd and nife was doing 227dd against undead, followed up by expulse undead at 95dd... not too shabby.... until..... i switched to Jawbone of Elder Wolf (LORE ITEM MAGIC ITEM <br>Damage: 11 <br>Delay: 29 <br>Ratio: 2.636 Excellent <br>Str: +2 Sta: +2 Dex: +2 Cha: -20 Magic Resist: +2 Fire Resist: +2 Cold Resist: +2 <br>Weight: 4.0 <br>Weapon Skill: One Hand Slash <br>Classes: Warrior Rogue Bard Shadowknight Paladin Ranger <br>Races: All Races <br>....upon switching to this wep the Nife buff processed consistantly.... much more so than with the Ghoul.... i was suprised... in doing the math i was doing more damage with the Jawbone than with the Ghoul... just because if the rate at whivh Nife processed for 227 dd everytime...... WOW.....(Just make sure to unequip the Jawbone when selling or buying....-20 char..hehe) I am not sure of the math but with the Nife processing almost every other time i was swinging at the undead.... its proc rate trounces the Ghoulbane... i think i will retire the Ghoul to the bank for my epic....( <br><br>If you are on the Drinal Server and want to do something send me a tell. <br><br>Sincerely, <br><br>Runtiss<br> <br><br>&nbsp;<br> </td></tr>
